<TEXT>
burundis foreign minister said sunday that 
authorities had stopped the violence in that central african 
nation where at least 5000 people were killed in battles between 
rival tribes 
cyprien mbonimpa told reporters there are currently no more 
killings no more bloodshed 
he spoke to reporters after an hourlong meeting with un 
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar 
mbonimpa replying to a question said burundi would not accept 
an international inquiry into the killings by members of the hutu 
and tutsi tribes that began two weeks ago 
he said he had asked perez de cuellars backing for burundis 
appeal for 15 million in emergency aid with the money to provide 
food and clothing for three months for 100000 people left homeless 
mbonimpa said people displaced inside burundi are returning 
hour by hour to their villages 
more than 40000 people fled into neighoring rwanda to escape 
the massacres 
the hutu and tutsi have been rivals for centuries the hutu form 
a majority in burundi but the tutsi tribe dominates the government 
and army 
mbonimpa said the death toll may be higher than the 5000 
reported last monday by the government but there is no new official 
figure 
the violence began aug 14 in two communities in northern 
burundi according to refugees in rwanda 
they said army units controlled by tutsi officers were sent 
north to restore peace and the soldiers opened fire on the hutu 
mbonimpa repeated a claim by burundis leader maj pierre 
buyoya who last week blamed the massacres on dissident hutus he 
said infiltrated burundi from tanzania and provoked antitutsi 
actions 
when the rebels had already killed thousands the army was 
ordered to intervene he told reporters at the un office in 
geneva he did not elaborate on who the rebels were or where they 
came from 
certainly there were dead people killed by soldiers because 
the army was obliged to use force to repulse the rebels he said 
the armys other mission was to protect and help those who were 
fleeing 
the burundi army is one of the most disciplined armies and 
there never is any loss of control he added to gain control 
of a situation in three days requires a disciplined and well 
controlled army 
</TEXT>
