iraq said sunday that iranian troops fired 
shots and set up new radar and observation posts last week in 
violation of a 9dayold truce in the persian gulf war 
iran accused iraq of undermining the peace talks in geneva by 
claiming sovereignty over the disputed shattalarab waterway and 
said the talks may drag on for years 
the commander of the un observer forces monitoring the truce 
said the ceasefire was holding but that more time was needed to 
finish plotting the exact location of the front line 
the official iraqi news agency said more than a dozen iranian 
violations were reported to the un peacekeepers between tuesday 
and friday neither iran nor the observer force commented on the 
claims 
in the northern region of kurdistan the iranians set up two 
radar positions manned by three iranian officers not far from 
iraqi troops the agency said it said appropriate measures were 
taken to eliminate the two positions and push the enemy back but 
did not elaborate 
at the southern end of the front iranian soldiers fired shots 
but un observers intervened to stop the iranian violations and 
returned two advancing iranians to their positions the agency 
said 
in other parts of the front the iranians set up barricades 
fired a machine gun flew helicopters near iraqi positions and set 
up other radar and observation posts the agency said 
irans official islamic republic news agency monitored in 
cyprus quoted deputy foreign minister javad mansouri as saying 
iraq continues to have designs on irans territorial integrity 
