corp and one share of stock in pride petroleum services inc the 
oilwell servicing company for each share of dekalb corp stock 
dekalb corp then will be renamed dekalb energy co and will 
concentrate on oil and gas exploration 
finally the company plans an initial public offering of the 
lindsay manufacturing co its wholly owned irrigation 
manufacturing and marketing division john stafford dekalbs chief 
financial officer said the lindsay offering is tentatively planned 
for september but the date will depend on market conditions and 
the timing of regulatory approval 
dekalb currently has two types of stock class a voting stock 
which is not publicly traded and class b nonvoting stock which 
is publicly traded the roberts family which founded dekalb in the 
1930s controls 60 percent of the class a stock and thus controls 
the company 
after the split the roberts family will retain control of 
dekalb energy and dekalb genetics but pride petroleum will have 
only one class of stock all voting only 20 percent of that stock 
will be owned by the roberts family 
the family is retaining its absolute control of the genetics 
and energy business but giving up absolute control of pride 
bickner said 
analysts have estimated the aggregate value of the companies 
after the spinoff at 34 to 40 a share dekalb energy is expected 
to trade around 20 a share dekalb genetics at about 10 and 
dekalb corp at around 7 
in addition to demonstrating the importance of analyst coverage 
to a stocks value dekalbs breakup illustrates the declining 
popularity among investors of conglomerates in favor of socalled 
pure plays companies with only one line of business 
i think the last time it was an advantage to be a conglomerate 
was in the late 60s in the late 60s they were magic said 
strain 
analyst harris agreed 
twenty years ago there was a mindset among corporate 
executives that they were going to be portfolio managers they 
would buy and sell companies and get big and diversify and that was 
good he said 
but in the last few years its finally dawned on people that 
managers should not be portfolio managers harris added they 
should run businesses and let the investors arrange their own 
portfolios 
</TEXT>
